AWKA – Governor Chukwuma Charles Soludo has expressed readi­ness of the state government to partner with the World Health Organisation (WHO) in pro­viding quality and affordable healthcare to Anambra people. A statement released to journalists by the governor’s Chief Press Secretary (CPS), Mr. Christian Aburime, had it that the governor made the disclosure when he received in audience, the WHO Repre­sentative in Nigeria, Dr. Walter Mulombo, who was a visit with members of his team at the Governor’s Lodge in Amawbia at the weekend. According to Soludo, his ad­ministration was committed to having a healthy and produc­tive population, pointing out that WHO had a pivotal role to play in that regard. The statement also dis­closed that Soludo, who stressed that his administra­tion had begun to deliver a bit of the agenda as contained in his manifesto, pleaded with the visiting WHO Represen­tative to add Anambra in its agenda and assistance to states. It said that the governor made special mention of the efforts of WHO in eradication of tropical diseases which had adversely affected the African populace.